ukResidency.nonUkResidentPurchaser.title                                            = Residency status
ukResidency.nonUkResidentPurchaser.heading                                          = Residency status
ukResidency.nonUkResidentPurchaser.subheading                                       = Are any of the purchasers non-UK residents?
ukResidency.nonUkResidentPurchaser.p1                                               = A purchaser is considered a non-UK resident for the purposes of SDLT if they spent fewer than 183 days in the UK during the 12 months before the effective date of the transaction.
ukResidency.nonUkResidentPurchaser.p2                                               = Read the latest <a href="{0}" class="govuk-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">{1}</a>.
ukResidency.nonUkResidentPurchaser.hint.link                                        = https://www.gov.uk/guidance/rates-of-stamp-duty-land-tax-for-non-uk-residents
ukResidency.nonUkResidentPurchaser.hint.suffix                                      = HMRC guidance on residence status for SDLT (opens in a new tab)
ukResidency.nonUkResidentPurchaser.checkYourAnswersLabel                            = Are any of the purchasers non-UK residents?
ukResidency.nonUkResidentPurchaser.error.required                                   = Select yes if any of the purchasers are non-UK residents
ukResidency.nonUkResidentPurchaser.change.hidden                                    = Are any of the purchasers non-UK residents?

ukResidency.crownEmploymentRelief.title                                             = Crown employment relief
ukResidency.crownEmploymentRelief.heading                                           = Crown employment relief
ukResidency.crownEmploymentRelief.subheading                                        = Are any of the purchasers claiming Crown employment relief?
ukResidency.crownEmploymentRelief.p1                                                = Relief from the non-UK surcharge is available if purchasers are not resident in the UK due to holding an office or employment under the Crown, such as a member of the UK armed forces, a civil servant or a diplomat. This relief is extended to the spouse or civil partner of a crown servant, provided they are not separated.
ukResidency.crownEmploymentRelief.checkYourAnswersLabel                             = Are any of the purchasers claiming Crown employment relief?
ukResidency.crownEmploymentRelief.missing                                           = Select if any purchasers are claiming Crown employment relief
ukResidency.crownEmploymentRelief.error.required                                    = Select yes if any of the purchasers are claiming Crown employment relief
ukResidency.crownEmploymentRelief.change.hidden                                     = Are any of the purchasers claiming Crown employment relief?

ukResidency.closeCompany.title                                                      = Close companies
ukResidency.closeCompany.heading                                                    = Close companies
ukResidency.closeCompany.subheading                                                 = Are any of the purchasers a UK resident close company controlled directly or non-directly by non-UK residents?
ukResidency.closeCompany.p1                                                         = A close company is broadly defined as a company controlled by five or fewer participators (usually shareholders), or where any number of directors are also shareholders. If the company is controlled by non-UK residents, then it will be treated as a non-UK resident for the purposes of SDLT.
ukResidency.closeCompany.checkYourAnswersLabel                                      = Are any of the purchasers a UK resident close company controlled directly or non-directly by non-UK residents?
ukResidency.closeCompany.error.required                                             = Select yes if any of the purchasers are a UK resident close company controlled directly or non-directly by non-UK residents
ukResidency.closeCompany.change.hidden                                              = Are any of the purchasers a UK resident close company controlled directly or non-directly by non-UK residents?

ukResidency.ukResident                                                              = UK resident
ukResidency.nonUkResident                                                           = Non-UK resident

