transaction.ReasonForRelief.change.hidden                                           = Reason for claiming relief
transaction.ReasonForRelief.missing                                                 = Enter the reason for claiming relief

taxCalculation.checkYourAnswers.title                                               = Check your answers - Tax calculation
taxCalculation.checkYourAnswers.continue                                            = Confirm and continue
taxCalculation.checkYourAnswers.declaration                                         = Declaration
taxCalculation.checkYourAnswers.declaration.text                                    = By continuing, I confirm that all details provided in this return are accurate. I understand that any errors can affect the amount of SDLT due and may result in penalties and interest charges.

taxCalculation.beforeStart.title.freehold.taxCalculated                             = Before you start - Tax calculation - Freehold calculated
taxCalculation.beforeStart.title.freehold.taxNotCalculated                          = Before you start - Tax calculation - Freehold not calculated
taxCalculation.beforeStart.title.leasehold.taxCalculated                            = Before you start - Tax calculation - Leasehold calculated
taxCalculation.beforeStart.title.leasehold.taxNotCalculated                         = Before you start - Tax calculation - Leasehold not calculated
taxCalculation.beforeStart.selfAssessed.bullet                                      = your self-assessed SDLT calculation
taxCalculation.beforeStart.p1                                                       = In this section, you need to provide information about your tax calculation.
taxCalculation.beforeStart.p2                                                       = You will need to know:
taxCalculation.beforeStart.bullet1                                                  = the tax due on the total premium payable
taxCalculation.beforeStart.bullet2                                                  = the tax due on the NPV
taxCalculation.beforeStart.bullet3                                                  = the amount you intend to pay with this return
taxCalculation.beforeStart.bullet4                                                  = if this amount includes penalties and fines

taxCalculation.calculatedSdltDue.title                                              = Calculated SDLT due
taxCalculation.calculatedSdltDue.heading                                            = Calculated SDLT due is {0}
taxCalculation.calculatedSdltDue.p1                                                 = The amount of SDLT due is based on the information you have entered when filing this return.
taxCalculation.calculatedSdltDue.linkText                                           = Check your SDLT breakdown
taxCalculation.calculatedSdltDue.checkYourAnswersLabel                              = HMRC calculated SDLT due

taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.title                                         = HMRC cannot calculate the SDLT due
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.heading                                       = HMRC cannot calculate the SDLT due
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.p1                                            = The amount of SDLT due cannot be calculated because {0}
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.p1.withColon                                  = The amount of SDLT due cannot be calculated because:
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.noReason.p1                                   = The amount of SDLT due cannot be calculated.
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.noReason.p2                                   = Select ‘Continue’ to enter the self-assessed amount of SDLT due.
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.reason1                                       = this return includes linked transactions. This means that HMRC does not have full visibility of each transaction.
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.reason2                                       = this return includes a claim for partial relief. The tax due on partial relief depends on value judgements that can only be made by the purchaser.
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.reason3                                       = this return includes a type of interest that falls outside of the SDLT calculation model.
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.reason4                                       = this return includes a claim for Multiple Dwellings Relief. The tax due on this relief depends on the purchaser declaring the number of dwellings.
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.reason5                                       = this return predates the modern SDLT calculation model. This is because:
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.reason5.b1                                    = the property type is ‘01 - Residential’ or ‘04 - Additional residential property liable to higher rate’
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.reason5.b2                                    = the effective date of the transaction is before 22 March 2012
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.reason6                                       = this return includes a claim for ‘25 - Collective enfranchisement by leaseholders’ relief. The tax calculation for this relief is complex and relies on information HMRC can’t verify.
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.reason7                                       = this return predates the modern SDLT calculation model. This is because:
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.reason7.b1                                    = the effective date of the transaction is between 25 March 2010 and 25 March 2012
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.reason7.b2                                    = the type of transaction is ‘L - Grant of lease’
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.reason7.b3                                    = ‘32 - First Time Buyer’s Relief’ is being claimed
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.reason8                                       = this return predates the modern SDLT calculation model. This is because:
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.reason8.b1                                    = the effective date of the transaction is between 12 March 2008 and 17 March 2016
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.reason8.b2                                    = the type of property is ‘02 - Mixed’
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.reason8.b3                                    = the annual rent is £1,000 or more
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.multipleReasons.b1                            = this return includes linked transactions – this means that HMRC does not have full visibility of each transaction
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.multipleReasons.b2                            = this return includes a claim for partial relief – the tax due on partial relief depends on value judgements that can only be made by the purchaser
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.multipleReasons.b3                            = this return includes a type of interest that falls outside of the SDLT calculation model
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.multipleReasons.b4                            = this return includes a claim for ‘33 - Multiple Dwellings Relief’ – the tax due on this relief depends on the purchaser declaring the number of dwellings
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.multipleReasons.b5                            = the effective date of the transaction is before 22 March 2012 – this predates the modern SDLT calculation model for residential properties
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.multipleReasons.b6                            = this return includes a claim for ‘25 - Collective enfranchisement by leaseholders’ relief – the tax calculation for this relief is complex and relies on information HMRC can’t verify
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.multipleReasons.b7                            = ‘32 - First Time Buyer’s Relief’ is being claimed on a residential property with transaction type ‘L - Grant of lease’ and an effective date of the transaction between 25 March 2010 and 25 March 2012 – this predates the modern SDLT calculation model
taxCalculation.cannotCalculateSdltDue.multipleReasons.b8                            = the type of property is ‘02 - Mixed’, the annual rent is £1,000 or more and the effective date of the transaction is between 12 March 2008 and 17 March 2016 – this predates the modern SDLT calculation model

