taxCalculation.sdltSelfAssessment.title                                             = SDLT self-assessment
taxCalculation.sdltSelfAssessment.heading                                           = SDLT self-assessment
taxCalculation.sdltSelfAssessment.intro                                             = SDLT is a self-assessed tax. The legal responsibility for calculating, reporting and paying the correct amount rests with the purchaser of the land or property.
taxCalculation.sdltSelfAssessment.warning                                           = HMRC expects each person to take reasonable care when calculating tax, including creating and preserving records, to provide a complete and accurate return.
taxCalculation.sdltSelfAssessment.calculator                                        = You can <a href="{0}" class="govuk-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">{1}</a>.
taxCalculation.sdltSelfAssessment.calculator.link                                   = https://www.tax.service.gov.uk/calculate-stamp-duty-land-tax/
taxCalculation.sdltSelfAssessment.calculator.text                                   = use the SDLT calculator to work out the correct amount (opens in a new tab)
taxCalculation.sdltSelfAssessment.h2                                                = What is the self-assessed amount of SDLT?
taxCalculation.sdltSelfAssessment.hint                                              = Enter the amount in whole pounds only, for example £10,000. This amount should not include any penalties or interest due.

